DIFFERENCES BETWEEN ACTUAL AND EXPECTED RETURNS CAN AFFECT FUTURE YEARS PENSION COST. THE ASSET BALANCE USED TO CALCULATE THE EXPECTED RETURN ON PENSION PLAN ASSETS IS A CALCULATED VALUE THAT RECOGNIZES CHANGES IN THE FAIR VALUE OF

ASSETS OVER A FIVE YEAR PERIOD. DESPITE INVESTMENT GAINS DURING 2009, THE SIGNIFICANT LOSSES INCURRED DURING 2008 WILL CAUSE NET PERIODIC PENSION COST FOR 2010 TO INCREASE BY APPROXIMATELY $100 MILLION DUE TO AMORTIZATION OF ACTUARIAL LOSSES. ABSENT

A RECOVERY OF ASSET VALUES OR HIGHER INTEREST RATES OR HIGHER CONTRIBUTIONS, NET PERIODIC PENSION EXPENSE WILL INCREASE FURTHER IN FUTURE YEARS.

